reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality replacement ink for Canon Printers
reviews.reviewText: I've have bought two sets of this ink, and they work great in my Cannon MX922 printer.Note: this is not OEM Canon ink. However this is a high quality ink that works great, and is much more affordable the Canon ink.I printed out a photo on glossy paper, which came out great.If you see the text is fading, stop printing immediately and replace your ink.If you see double characters, it is likely you need to replace the print head. You can get a new OEM print head by calling Canon Parts (for about $100). Search for "ordering Canon Parts". You cannot order them online, but you can order them by calling the Canon Parts number. Also consider buying a printer strip at the same time ($2 more).

reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars KNOCK OFF CARTIDGES - PRINTER WILL NOT RECOGNIZE THEY ARE INSTALLED
reviews.reviewText: WHEN I CHANGED THE PRINT CARTRIDGES THE PRINTER WILL NOT RECOGNIZE THESE CARTRIDGES - THERE SHOULD BE TWO PROTRUSIONS AT THE END OF THE CARTRIDGE - THERE IS ONLY 1 - BECAUSE OF THIS THE PRINTER WILL NOT RECOGNIZE THAT A NEW CARTRIDGE WAS INSTALLED. THE CARTRIDGE ON THE LEFT CAME WITH THE PRINTER - THE CARTRIDGE ON THE RIGHT IS WHAT I BOUGHT FOR REFILLS. I DO NOT RECOMMEND YOU USE THESE AS PRINTER WILL NOT RECOGNIZE THEY ARE INSTALLED
